                  "pages": [
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "Before the Weavers vanished, they left a promise in the stone: that one day, new Dreamers would arise to finish what they began.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "The promise is carved into bedrock, in a language that cannot be read \u2014 only felt. You have felt it. Every time you stand on the edge of a cliff and feel the urge to build, that is the promise calling.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "Every time you look at a landscape and think 'this could be more,' you are hearing the Weavers' voice, still echoing after all this time.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
